                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>John Hays Hammond, American citizen, said to be held for treason at Johannesburg,
                    Africa. Mention matter unofficially to Lord Salisbury that necessary measures
                    for Hammond’s protection may be taken through British representative at
                    Pretoria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
